HEADWORD: Paragonite
<hw>Pa*rag"o*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Gr. <?/,
p. pr. of <?/ to mislead.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A kind of mica
related to muscovite, but containing soda instead of potash. It is
characteristic of the <partof>paragonite schist</partof> of the
Alps.</def>⟦br⟧
